631
00:39:33,434 --> 00:39:37,295
却没有新的能量或热量进入系统
And there is no new energy or heat coming into that system.

632
00:39:38,253 --> 00:39:40,614
如果宇宙不停止自身的扩张
If the universe doesn't tear itself apart first,

633
00:39:40,808 --> 00:39:43,558
宇宙会终结为一个极冻的世界
the universe will end as a deep freeze

634
00:39:43,878 --> 00:39:47,156
--寒冷、黑暗而且压抑
-- Cold... dark... and depressing.

635
00:39:50,169 --> 00:39:51,713
太阳们烧光
Narrator: Suns burn out.

636
00:39:52,892 --> 00:39:54,378
行星们被毁灭
Planets are destroyed.

637
00:39:57,919 --> 00:40:02,961
星系碰撞、坍塌、燃烧，然后散架
Galaxies collide, collapse, ignite, then fall apart--

638
00:40:03,683 --> 00:40:06,128
冰块四处飘散
Frozen shells of their former selves.

639
00:40:08,905 --> 00:40:11,252
在几百个数十亿年之后
Over hundreds of billions of years,

640
00:40:11,433 --> 00:40:14,863
宇宙的每一点能量都被利用了
every bit of energy in our universe gets used up

641
00:40:15,725 --> 00:40:18,211
--消失在无限扩张的太空
--Lost to the ever-expanding void

642
00:40:18,919 --> 00:40:24,252
宇宙的熵会达到致命的最大状态
as the entropy of our universe reaches a final fatal maximum state.

643
00:40:27,238 --> 00:40:29,266
最终，它会扩张到极点
Eventually, it will expand to the point

644
00:40:29,335 --> 00:40:31,933
届时将没有热量留在宇宙里
where there will be no heat left in the universe.

645
00:40:32,335 --> 00:40:33,822
这意味着没有化学反应
That means no chemical reactions.

646
00:40:34,238 --> 00:40:35,807
意味着没有生物作用
That means no biological reactions.

647
00:40:36,002 --> 00:40:37,460
你看到的将是
What you will see is

648
00:40:40,849 --> 00:40:44,960
--宇宙的最终阶段看起来什么也没有...
-- The final state of our universe is really just going to look like a whole lot of nothing...

649
00:40:45,335 --> 00:40:48,543
什么也看不到--没有黑洞，没有白矮星
Nothing to see here-- No black holes, no white dwarf stars,

650
00:40:48,599 --> 00:40:50,182
没有中子星
no neutron stars.

651
00:40:50,516 --> 00:40:52,335
即使是质子也没有...
Not even any protons...

652
00:40:53,168 --> 00:40:54,766
什么都没有
Just nothing.

653
00:40:55,710 --> 00:40:58,863
一个非常寒冷、非常黑暗的宇宙
In a very cold, dark universe,

654
00:40:59,071 --> 00:41:02,196
你会说，这会是终极的深冻
you could say that this will be the ultimate deep freeze.

655
00:41:04,238 --> 00:41:06,113
这是必然的吗？
Narrator: But does it have to be that way?

656
00:41:07,376 --> 00:41:09,988
有什么能让宇宙避免最终成为
Is there anything that could prevent our universe

657
00:41:10,099 --> 00:41:12,890
一个冰冻、黑暗的虚空吗？
from ending up as a frozen, dark void?

658
00:41:14,043 --> 00:41:17,626
要避免宇宙的终极死亡
In order to prevent an ultimate death of the universe,

659
00:41:17,932 --> 00:41:21,932
重力--或者其它类似于重力的奇异力量
gravity-- or some attractive force like gravity

660
00:41:22,112 --> 00:41:26,557
--必须把宇宙所有的子民拉扯回来
-- will have to pull back together all the constituents of the universe.

661
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:29,279
现在的宇宙正在扩张
Right now the universe is expanding.

662
00:41:29,293 --> 00:41:31,765
我们测量到的重力
And the force of gravity as we measure

663
00:41:31,793 --> 00:41:34,348
并不足以把一切拉扯在一起
it isn't enough to pull everything together.

664
00:41:34,793 --> 00:41:38,557
但要知道，我们还不能完全知道所有的作用力
But we recognize that we don't even know all the players at work.

665
00:41:38,584 --> 00:41:42,612
在过去的20年，我们才认识到暗能量
It's only been the last 20 years that we've even known that dark energy

666
00:41:43,112 --> 00:41:47,640
这是一种令人讨厌的力量，它会分散宇宙
-- which is a repulsive force in essence, something that pushes the universe apart

667
00:41:48,181 --> 00:41:51,737
--我们在20年之前甚至不知道它的存在
-- We didn't even know it existed more than about 20 years ago.

668
00:41:52,209 --> 00:41:54,202
有可能在某一天
But it's conceivable that some day,

669
00:41:54,223 --> 00:41:57,598
加速宇宙扩张的暗能量
the dark energy that's accelerating the expansion of the universe

670
00:41:58,056 --> 00:42:00,167
摇身变为重力一样的吸引力
will become gravitationally attractive.

671
00:42:00,945 --> 00:42:03,570
果真如此，而且它是足够的话
If that's the case, and if there's enough of it,

672
00:42:04,001 --> 00:42:08,112
宇宙或会停止它的扩张，再次坍塌
then the universe may halt its expansion and re-collapse.

673
00:42:08,306 --> 00:42:10,834
我们不知道这会否发生，但它可能会发生
We don't know that that will happen, but it might happen.

674
00:42:11,223 --> 00:42:16,403
在那种情况下，宇宙会经历一次非常高温的热死亡
In that case, the universe will experience a really hot heat-death,

675
00:42:16,556 --> 00:42:20,431
所有微粒会骤然进入到其它微粒里面
where all the particles are slamming into all the other particles.

676
00:42:20,639 --> 00:42:21,848
温度很高
High temperatures.

677
00:42:21,903 --> 00:42:24,639
恒星走向毁灭，行星走向毁灭
Stars get destroyed, planets get destroyed.

678
00:42:24,764 --> 00:42:29,097
只剩下一个不同与往的、死气沉沉的宇宙...
You get a different form of a lifeless universe...

679
00:42:30,472 --> 00:42:34,056
一个以高温代替极冻的宇宙
One which is hot instead of in the deep freeze.

680
00:42:35,278 --> 00:42:38,250
但是，它不会形成“遮阳幕”
Narrator: Still, don't break out the sunscreen yet.

681
00:42:39,375 --> 00:42:44,472
我敢打赌，宇宙会最终成为非常低温的极冻世界...
My bet is that the universe will end up in a very low temperature deep freeze...

682
00:42:44,750 --> 00:42:48,208
因为目前的暗能量，看起来或许会
Because it seems that the current dark energy might be the type

683
00:42:48,472 --> 00:42:51,778
继续加速宇宙的扩张，永不停止
that will continue to accelerate the expansion forever.

684
00:42:52,319 --> 00:42:55,027
假如果真如此，宇宙的温度
If that's the case, the temperature of the universe

685
00:42:55,111 --> 00:43:00,583
会反复接近绝对零度这一终极寒冷的温度
will become arbitrarily close to absolute zero-- The ultimate deep freeze.

686
00:43:02,791 --> 00:43:06,014
寒冷是我们宇宙的一个决定性因素
Narrator: Cold is a critical ingredient of our universe.

687
00:43:06,888 --> 00:43:11,902
它是我们所见到的宇宙的必要组成
Cold is essential to having the universe that we see.

688
00:43:12,249 --> 00:43:15,708
因为如果没有寒冷，能量就不会流动
Because without a cold spot, energy doesn't flow.

689
00:43:15,749 --> 00:43:18,680
你需要能量从热流向冷
You need energy to flow from hot to cold.

690
00:43:19,138 --> 00:43:21,694
正是能量的流动
And it is the flow of energy that leads to

691
00:43:21,708 --> 00:43:25,708
才形成现在的宇宙万物，包括我们人类本身
all the structures that we see in the universe, including ourselves.

692
00:43:26,235 --> 00:43:30,777
所以，如果没有能量通过各种可能方式
So we wouldn't be here if energy weren't trying to flow

693
00:43:30,791 --> 00:43:34,221
竭力从热的地方流向宇宙各处
from hot concentrated organized places

694
00:43:34,263 --> 00:43:38,416
我们就不会在这里存在
into the many forms that it can flow into in the universe.

695
00:43:40,541 --> 00:43:44,596
因此，日后感到冬日的寒冷或是被雪球打中的时候
So the next time you feel a winter chill or get hit with a snowball,

696
00:43:44,777 --> 00:43:48,818
你要记住--如果不是寒冷，你就不会在这里
just remember-- If it weren't for cold, you wouldn't be here.

697
00:43:49,082 --> 00:43:52,019
而且，如果算是一丝安慰的话
And if it's any consolation, you won't be around

698
00:43:52,707 --> 00:43:56,179
现在的你不用花上几百个数万亿年
hundreds of trillions of years from now when the universe

699
00:43:56,304 --> 00:43:59,999
去陪同宇宙迎接最后的极冻结局
enters its final state of deep freeze.

